This module provides functionality to build a hierarchical tree structure from a flat list of documentation entries.

## Key Exports

- `FileNode`: Represents a file in the documentation tree. It includes properties like `kind`, `name`, `key`, and `title`.
- `FolderNode`: Represents a folder in the documentation tree. It includes properties like `kind`, `name`, and `children` (an array of `TreeNode`).
- `TreeNode`: A union type representing either a `FileNode` or a `FolderNode`.
- `buildTree(entries: ManifestEntry[]): TreeNode[]`: This is the main function that takes an array of `ManifestEntry` objects and constructs the documentation tree. It processes the `docKey` of each entry to determine its position in the hierarchy.

## Purpose

The primary purpose of this module is to transform a flat list of documentation entries, likely read from a manifest file, into a nested tree structure. This structure is ideal for representing file system-like hierarchies, which can then be used for navigation, display in UI components (like sidebars), or further processing.

## How it Works

The `buildTree` function iterates through each `ManifestEntry`. For each entry, it splits the `docKey` by `/` to extract path segments. It then traverses or creates `FolderNode`s corresponding to these segments, eventually placing the `FileNode` (representing the actual document) at its correct location within the tree. The `sortNodes` function is used to ensure that both folders and files within each level are sorted alphabetically, with folders appearing before files.

## Usage Example

```typescript
import type { ManifestEntry } from "../types";
import { buildTree, TreeNode } from "./tree";

// Assume manifestEntries is an array of ManifestEntry objects
const manifestEntries: ManifestEntry[] = [
  { docKey: "guide/getting-started", title: "Getting Started" },
  { docKey: "guide/installation", title: "Installation" },
  { docKey: "api/core/authentication", title: "Authentication API" },
  { docKey: "api/core/users", title: "Users API" },
  { docKey: "guide/advanced/configuration", title: "Advanced Configuration" },
];

const documentationTree: TreeNode[] = buildTree(manifestEntries);

console.log(JSON.stringify(documentationTree, null, 2));

/*
Output would look something like:
[
  {
    "kind": "folder",
    "name": "api",
    "children": [
      {
        "kind": "folder",
        "name": "core",
        "children": [
          {
            "kind": "file",
            "name": "authentication",
            "key": "api/core/authentication",
            "title": "Authentication API"
          },
          {
            "kind": "file",
            "name": "users",
            "key": "api/core/users",
            "title": "Users API"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "kind": "folder",
    "name": "guide",
    "children": [
      {
        "kind": "folder",
        "name": "advanced",
        "children": [
          {
